  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Support to FAHP for Celebration of International</narrative>
  </title>
  <description>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">The &#x2018;support to FAHP to celebrate the International Day of Zero Tolerance for Female Genital Mutilation&#x2019; in Sierra Leone, implemented by Forum Against Harmful Practices (FAHP) aims to raise awareness on the implication of FGM/C on girls and to advocate for sound policies and inspire more political commitment, investment and coordination. The objective for FAHP&#x2019;s commemoration of this day is to increase awareness of the dangers FGM can pose to the health and dignity of the girl child and to promote its eradication. The key activity is the one day national conference to show case FAHP&#x2019;s activities and to discuss strategies on the new rites of passage model (Bondo without blood).</narrative>
  </description>
